  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I'm on Jio network. I am able to watch Youtube videos cleanly without much buffering but downloading speed is pathetic",
  "response": "It's a common observation that streaming services like YouTube work well even on slower connections because they use adaptive bitrate streaming. This means the quality of the video adjusts automatically based on your available bandwidth. However, downloading files requires a consistent and sustained connection, which can be more challenging on networks with fluctuating speeds or congestion.\n\nHere are a few steps to troubleshoot and potentially improve your download speed on Jio:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Check Network Congestion**\n- **Peak hours**: Networks are often congested during peak hours (e.g., evenings). Try downloading during off-peak times (early morning or late night).\n- **Location**: If you're in a crowded area, network speeds might be slower. Move to a less congested location.\n\n---\n\n### **2. Restart Your Device**\n- Sometimes, simply restarting your phone or modem can resolve temporary network issues.\n\n---\n\n### **3. Check APN Settings**\n- Ensure your APN (Access Point Name) settings are correct. For Jio, the APN should be `jionet`. To check:\n  - Go to **Settings > Mobile Network > Access Point Names**.\n  - Ensure `jionet` is selected.\n\n---\n\n### **4. Test Speed**\n- Use a speed test app (like Ookla Speedtest) to check your download speed.\n- If the speed is significantly lower than what Jio advertises, there might be an issue with your connection.\n\n---\n\n### **5. Clear Cache and Data**\n- Clear the cache and data of the app you're using for downloading. Sometimes, corrupted cache can slow down downloads.\n\n---\n\n### **6. Use a Download Manager**\n- If you're downloading large files, use a download manager app. It can help resume interrupted downloads and improve efficiency.\n\n---\n\n### **7. Check Data Limit**\n- Ensure you haven't exceeded your daily or monthly data limit. Jio may throttle speeds after exhausting your high-speed data.\n\n---\n\n### **8. Switch to 4G/LTE**\n- Ensure you're connected to Jio's 4G/LTE network. If your phone is stuck on 3G, speeds will be slower.\n- To check: Go to **Settings > Mobile Network > Preferred Network Type** and select **4G/LTE**.\n\n---\n\n### **9. Contact Jio Customer Care**\n- If none of the above works, reach out to Jio customer care. There might be an issue with your SIM or network in your area.\n\n---\n\n### **10. Use Wi-Fi (if available)**\n- If possible, switch to a Wi-Fi connection for faster downloads.\n\n---\n\nIf YouTube works fine but downloads are slow, it\u2019s likely due to the difference in how streaming and downloading use bandwidth. However, following the above steps should help improve your download speed.",
